Description: A gifted visionary known for predicting the future. When summoned, look at the top 3 cards in your deck and replace them in any order you desire.
EffectText: Summon: Look at the top 3 cards of your Main Deck and put them back in any order.
ShortDescription: Summon: Look at the top 3 cards of your Main Deck and put them back in any order.

Description: A being said to be capable of speaking things into existence. When summoned, look at the top 3 cards in your opponents deck and replace them in any order you desire.
EffectText: Summon: Look at the top 3 cards of your opponent's Main Deck and put them back in any order.
ShortDescription: Summon: Look at the top 3 cards of your opponent's Main Deck and put them back in any order.

Description: A wizard capable of venturing to the land beyond and bringing back that which was lost. Add one card from your graveyard to your hand when this Hero is Summoned.
EffectText: Summon: Add a card from your Graveyard to your hand.
ShortDescription: Summon: Add a card from your Graveyard to your hand.

Description: A notoriously studious individuals who is said to know all. Pick 1 card from your opponents hand or field to view each turn.
EffectText: Periodic: View 1 card of your choice in your opponent's hand.
ShortDescription: Periodic: View 1 card of your choice in your opponent's hand.

Description: A mysterious figure who keeps mostly to the shadows. Their identity and machinations are unknown even to the most devout of lorekeepers. You may replace one card in your hand with a random card from your Deck once per turn.
EffectText: Periodic: Exchange 1 card from your hand with a random card from your Main Deck.
ShortDescription: Periodic: Exchange 1 card from your hand with a random card from your Main Deck.

Description: A sorcerer whose tampering with the Forbidden Arts has led him down a dark path. He frequently clashes with the White Sage. Steal one magic card from your opponents deck when Summoned.
EffectText: Summon: Add 1 Magic card from your opponent's Main Deck to your hand.
ShortDescription: Summon: Add 1 Magic card from your opponent's Main Deck to your hand.

Description: A paragon of light whose shining example has been an inspiration for many Apprentices that came after him. He frequently clashes with the Dark Sage. Select one Magic card from your deck and add it to your hand when Summoned.
EffectText: Summon: Add 1 Magic card from your Main Deck to your hand.
ShortDescription: Summon: Add 1 Magic card from your Main Deck to your hand.

Description: The original Grand Elder who guided his people out of the Dark Ages. If you have an activatable Tech card you may play it for free the turn this Hero is Summoned.
EffectText: Summon: ??????
ShortDescription: Summon: ??????

Description: He has spent lifetimes taking the very concept of strength further than any before him. He's still seeking something more. Cannot be destroyed by Battle.
EffectText: Does not take battle damage.
ShortDescription: Does not take battle damage.

Description: Rebirth: Player can choose to immediately reshuffle the cards from their Medical Bay back into their Main Deck when this card is summoned.
EffectText: Summon: You may reshuffle your Medical Bay back into your Main Deck.
ShortDescription: Summon: You may reshuffle your Medical Bay back into your Main Deck.

Description: Never Lost A Battle: Add a Token to this card when summoned and anytime this card defeats an enemy Fighter by Battle. Anytime this card would have its Health reduced to zero, remove a Token from this card and restore Health back to original value. This card cannot be defeated by Battle until its Health is zero and it has no remaining Tokens attached to it.
EffectText: Summon/Event: Add a token to this card. Add another token whenever this card defeats a fighter. Any time this card has 0 HP, remove a token and restore its original HP. This card cannot be removed from the field until it has no tokens on it and is defeated.
ShortDescription: Summon/Event: Add a token to this card. Add another token whenever this card defeats a fighter. Any time this card has 0 HP, remove a token and restore its original HP. This card cannot be removed from the field until it has no tokens on it and is defeated.

Description: When in the Reinforcement Zone, at the start of every Battle Phase, Darwin can increase the Attack of the Player's current Fighter by +1.
EffectText: Periodic (Battle): When reinforcing, increase the Fighter's Attack by 1.
ShortDescription: Periodic (Battle): When reinforcing, increase the Fighter's Attack by 1.

Description: Classical: When Mozart is on the field and a non-Hero card's effects activate, they activate twice. After an effect activates once, treat it as if all conditions are met to immediately activate it a second time.
EffectText: Event: When a non-Hero card's effects activate, it activates twice.
ShortDescription: Event: When a non-Hero card's effects activate, it activates twice.

Description: Baroque: When Beethoven is summoned, the Figher immediately gains +3 Attack and +3 Health for every active, set card of any type.
EffectText: Summon: All set cards give your Fighter 3 Health and 3 Attack each.
ShortDescription: Summon: All set cards give your Fighter 3 Health and 3 Attack each.

Description: While this card remains on the field all Summon Crest dice rolls gain a +1 bonus. During the End Phase, add 1 Token to the Player's total. When this card is removed from the field decrease the Player's summon crests by an amount equal to the Token count.
EffectText:
Periodic: Gain 1 summon crest and 1 token.  

Summon: When this card leaves the field, subtract your token count from your crest amount.
ShortDescription:
Periodic: Gain 1 summon crest and 1 token.  

Summon: When this card leaves the field, subtract your token count from your crest amount.

Description: Player may summon as many Mongol cards as they can fill in the open Reinforcement slots upon summoning this card. While this card remains on the field, Mongol reinforcements can also serve in the role of the Fighter and target any opposing Fighter or Reinforcement card for attack. Player's Ranged Attribute cards gain +1 Attack while this card is on the Field
EffectText:
Summon (Deck/Hand): Fill all of your Reinforcment slots with Mongol cards.

Periodic (Battle): Mongol cards may act as additional Fighters and attack any opposing Fighter or Reinforcements. All Ranged Attacks are 1 higher while this card is on the field.
ShortDescription:
Summon (Deck/Hand): Fill all of your Reinforcment slots with Mongol cards.

Periodic (Battle): Mongol cards may act as additional Fighters and attack any opposing Fighter or Reinforcements. All Ranged Attacks are 1 higher while this card is on the field.

Description: Nihilism: Half of the damage inflicted by this card is reflected back on itself.
EffectText: Event: Reduce this card's HP by half of all damage it inflicts.
ShortDescription: Event: Reduce this card's HP by half of all damage it inflicts.

Description: While this card remains in either Player's Medical Bay, boost the Attack stat of the card's original owner by +1.
EffectText: Periodic: When in your Medical Bay, add 1 to the Attack of the Fighter used by this card's original owner.
ShortDescription: Periodic: When in your Medical Bay, add 1 to the Attack of the Fighter used by this card's original owner.

Description: Decreases the Summon Cost of any of the Player's Summoned or Activated cards by 1 while on the field.
EffectText: Periodic: Decrease all Costs by 1.
ShortDescription: Periodic: Decrease all Costs by 1.

Description: Name one Attribute. Both Players can only summon Normal/Hero cards of that Attribute as long as this card remains on the field.
EffectText: Periodic: Choose An attribute. Only cards of that Attribute can be summoned.
ShortDescription: Periodic: Choose An attribute. Only cards of that Attribute can be summoned.

Description: I am not a crook: When this card is summoned, your opponent must attempt to guess the name of the card at the bottom of your Medical Bay. If they guess correctly, your current fighter loses half their original attack and health stat. Otherwise the Player may draw any card from either player's Main Deck, Medical Bay, or Graveyard and put it in your hand.
EffectText: Summon: Your opponent must guess the name of the card at the bottom of your Medical Bay. If they guess correctly, your Fighter loses half their original Attack and HP. Otherwise, add any card from either player's Main Deck, Medical Bay, or Graveyard to your hand.
ShortDescription: Summon: Your opponent must guess the name of the card at the bottom of your Medical Bay. If they guess correctly, your Fighter loses half their original Attack and HP. Otherwise, add any card from either player's Main Deck, Medical Bay, or Graveyard to your hand.

Description: When summoned the Player has the option to add Merlin and/or the Knights of the Round Table from their Deck or Hand to any open Reinforcement slot on the player's side of the field. Additionally, equip Excalibur from Deck or Hand. Card Costs are ignored.
EffectText: Reflects damage inflicted on own reinforcers while on field.
ShortDescription: Reflects damage inflicted on own reinforcers while on field.

Description: When reinforcing King Arthur roll a pair of dice at the beginning of the Battle Phase. If the sum of the roll is at least 8, King Arthur becomes immune from taking battle damage for the remainder of the Phase.
EffectText: Swap the opposing Fighter with an enemy reinforcer of your choice.
ShortDescription: Swap the opposing Fighter with an enemy reinforcer of your choice.

Description: Must be Fusion Summoned if another "Knight of the Round Table" card is on your side of the field. The Attack and Health stat of the newly summoned card is added to that of the card it was fused with.
EffectText: Inflict damage on the opposing Fighter equal to the attack power of this card once per turn when a Normal or Hero card is captured.
ShortDescription: Inflict damage on the opposing Fighter equal to the attack power of this card once per turn when a Normal or Hero card is captured.

Description: Player gains +1 Life Point per Turn while on the field.
EffectText: Periodic: +1 LP when on field.
ShortDescription: Periodic: +1 LP when on field.

Description: Fighter gains +1 Health per Turn while this card remains on the field in a Reinforcement slot.
EffectText: Periodic: Gain 1 health if reinforcing.
ShortDescription: Periodic: Gain 1 health if reinforcing.

Description: Loses 3 Health during the End Phase of the Player's Turn.
EffectText: Periodic (End): Lose 3 health.
ShortDescription: Periodic (End): Lose 3 health.

Description: Gains 2 Attack per Turn while on the field.
EffectText: Periodic: Gain 2 Attack when on the field.
ShortDescription: Periodic: Gain 2 Attack when on the field.

Description: Pilgrimage to Mecca: At the start of the Game, the original Owner of this card gains 20 Summon Crests.
EffectText: Event (Start of Game): This card's original owner gains 20 summon crests.
ShortDescription: Event (Start of Game): This card's original owner gains 20 summon crests.

Description: Proletariat-Focused: When summoned, the opponent's fighter's current attack and health become equal to your fighter's current attack and health.
EffectText: Summon: The enemy Fighter's Attack and HP become equal to your Fighter's Attack and HP.
ShortDescription: Summon: The enemy Fighter's Attack and HP become equal to your Fighter's Attack and HP.

Description: Boosts the Attack of all Ranged allies by +2 while on the field.
EffectText: Periodic: Treat all Ranged Attack values as if they are 2 higher.
ShortDescription: Periodic: Treat all Ranged Attack values as if they are 2 higher.

Description: Red Fever: Reduce the health of all enemies by 5 when Lenin is summoned
EffectText: Summon: Reduce the health of all enemies on the field by 5.
ShortDescription: Summon: Reduce the health of all enemies on the field by 5.

Description: Unyielding: When Churchill is on the field and one of your fighters is defeated, roll a die. If you roll a 4 or higher, put your defeated fighter in your own Medical Bay instead of your opponent's.
Imitation Game: Once per Turn, the Player may choose one Hero card on the field, Medical Bay, or Graveyard. Imitate it's effect.
The Player may resurrect 1 card from the Graveyard per Turn during the Standby Phase.
EffectText: Once per turn add 1 Token to this card. As long as the card has a Token it cannot be damaged by battle. Inflict damage on opposing Fighter equal to the current number of Tokens on this card.
ShortDescription: Once per turn add 1 Token to this card. As long as the card has a Token it cannot be damaged by battle. Inflict damage on opposing Fighter equal to the current number of Tokens on this card.

Description: Zeus' attacks damage all enemy cards on the field. If sharing the field with another Olympian, Zeus can strike from any position on the field. In the event that another Olympian on the Player's field is defeating while Zeus is in play, target a random card from your Opponent's hand and add it to your Medical Bay.
EffectText: Attacks inflict damage on all enemies.
ShortDescription: Attacks inflict damage on all enemies.

Description: Ares gains Attack and Health equal to the combined amount of his Reinforcements during the Battle Phase.
EffectText: When summoned, gain bonus attack power equal to the number of cards in your MedBay.
ShortDescription: When summoned, gain bonus attack power equal to the number of cards in your MedBay.

Description: Lowers the Attack of Opposing Fighter by -2 while on the field.
EffectText: When summoned, paralyze the opposing Fighter. They can no longer attack.
ShortDescription: When summoned, paralyze the opposing Fighter. They can no longer attack.

Description: Doubles the Fighter's stat-related Bonuses when summoned.
EffectText: On Summon, choose 1 of 3 randomly-selected equip cards to add to your hand.
ShortDescription: On Summon, choose 1 of 3 randomly-selected equip cards to add to your hand.

Description: Poseidon's attacks may either damage the enemy fighter or an enemy reinforcer.
EffectText: Swap the opposing Fighter with an enemy reinforcer of your choice.
ShortDescription: Swap the opposing Fighter with an enemy reinforcer of your choice.

Description: If another Olympian is defeated while Hera is on the field, she may immediately deal damage to all enemy cards on the field.
EffectText: Inflict damage on the opposing Fighter equal to the attack power of this card once per turn when a Normal or Hero card is captured.
ShortDescription: Inflict damage on the opposing Fighter equal to the attack power of this card once per turn when a Normal or Hero card is captured.

Description: Demeter grants your current fighter +1 health every round.
EffectText: Gains immortality when joined by at least 3 reinforcers.
ShortDescription: Gains immortality when joined by at least 3 reinforcers.

Description: Magic spells and equip cards have no effect while Athena is on the field.
EffectText: Magic cards have no effect.
ShortDescription: Magic cards have no effect.

Description: Artemis automatically captures any Creature cards she targets.
EffectText: Attacks inflict direct damage on opponent.
ShortDescription: Attacks inflict direct damage on opponent.

Description: Your current Fighter may attack twice if Hermes is on the field.
EffectText: Doubles effects that increase the number of attacks of this card.
ShortDescription: Doubles effects that increase the number of attacks of this card.

Description: When Hestia is summoned, summon a random Tech card from your Tech Deck.
EffectText: Play your next Tech Card on summon.
ShortDescription: Play your next Tech Card on summon.

Description: When Dionysus is on the field, all Traps that you set immediately activate as if their conditions were met.
EffectText: Activate all traps every turn when on field.
ShortDescription: Activate all traps every turn when on field.

Description: Rage Against the Dying of the Light: Upon being defeated, Cronos spawns 1 Giant Attribute card from the Player's Deck in his place on the field.
Player gains access to the Fire Technology Card when Prometheus is summoned (Activate Tech Card requirements are ignored).
When summoned the Player will choose to view either the top 3 cards in their Main Deck or the top 3 cards in their Opponents Main Deck. Replace them in any order the Player desires.
Gorgon's Eye: Roll a pair of dice whenver the Opponent summons a new Fighter to the field. If the total of the dice roll is below 7, the opposing Fighter is immediately sent to the Medical bay.
When summoned the Opponent must reveal their hand to the Player.
Returns to the Player's Hand during the End Phase. Summon crests used to play this card is restored upon resolving this effect.
EffectText: Gain 1 Fusion Level for every copy of card
ShortDescription: Gain 1 Fusion Level for every copy of card

Description: This card cannot be destroyed by Battle. It gains 2 Health per Turn while on the field.
When this card is defeated, the Player may capture one Magic or Trap card from the Opponent's Medical Bay and add it to their Hand.
When summoned the Player may steal one Equip card from the Opponent's field, Medical Bay, Deck, or Hand and add it to their Fighter.
EffectText: When summoned the Player may steal one Equip card from the Opponent's field, Medical Bay, Deck, or Hand and add it to their Fighter.
ShortDescription: When summoned the Player may steal one Equip card from the Opponent's field, Medical Bay, Deck, or Hand and add it to their Fighter.

Description: Once per Turn, the player may revive one card from either Player's Medical Bay or Graveyard and activate it on their field.
Once per Turn, flip a coin. If the result is Heads, heal one of the cards on your field for +5 health. If the result is tails, inflict 5 points of damage on the opposing Fighter.
EffectText: Periodic: Flip a coin. If heads, heal one card for 5 health. If tails, the enemy fighter takes 5 damage.
ShortDescription: Periodic: Flip a coin. If heads, heal one card for 5 health. If tails, the enemy fighter takes 5 damage.

Description: When sharing the field with King Arthur, gains +1 Attack. During the Standby Phase of the Player's Turn, roll a die. If the result is 1 or 6, Lancelot enters a state of "madness" over Guinevere and gains +3 Attack, but cannot Attack during the Battle Phase this Turn.
EffectText: All reinforcements are sent to MedBay while on field.
ShortDescription: All reinforcements are sent to MedBay while on field.

Description: Choose one card in the opponent's MedBay. Inflict damage equal to 20% of your Attack power.
EffectText: Choose one card in the opponent's MedBay. Inflict damage equal to 20% of your Attack power.
ShortDescription: Choose one card in the opponent's MedBay. Inflict damage equal to 20% of your Attack power.

Description: Once per turn, you may choose one Set card on the opponent's side of the field and view it. If it's a Trap card, dismantle and capture it.
Grants +1 to the Attack stat of a Normal or Hero card that the Player controls.
EffectText: Increases one of your cards' Attack by 1.
ShortDescription: Increases one of your cards' Attack by 1.

Description: Grants +2 to the Attack stat of a Normal or Hero card that the Player controls.
EffectText: Increases one of your cards' Attack by 2.
ShortDescription: Increases one of your cards' Attack by 2.

Description: Grants +3 to the Attack stat of your Fighter.
EffectText: Treat your fighter's Attack as if it was 3 higher.
ShortDescription: Treat your fighter's Attack as if it was 3 higher.

Description: Can only be Equipped to "King Arthur." All currently active allied Warriors gain +3 Attack. All currently active enemy Warriors lose -2 Attack.
EffectText: Only equippable to King Arthur. Treat the Attack of all allied Warriors as if they were 3 higher. Treat the Attack of all enemy Warriors as if they were 2 lower.
ShortDescription: Only equippable to King Arthur. Treat the Attack of all allied Warriors as if they were 3 higher. Treat the Attack of all enemy Warriors as if they were 2 lower.

Description: Grants +3 to the Attack stat of a Normal or Hero Ranged-Type card that the Player controls.
EffectText: Increases one of your Ranged cards' Attack by 3.
ShortDescription: Increases one of your Ranged cards' Attack by 3.

Description: Grants +4 to the Attack stat of a Normal or Hero Ranged-Type card that the Player controls.
EffectText: Increases one of your Ranged cards' Attack by 4.

Description: Grants +7 to the Attack stat of a Normal or Hero Scientist-Type card that the Player controls.
EffectText: Increases one of your Scientist cards' Attack by 7.
ShortDescription: Increases one of your Scientist cards' Attack by 7.

Description: The next Normal/Hero card you Summon gets +3 Attack.
EffectText: Increases the Attack of the next card you summon by 3.
ShortDescription: Increases the Attack of the next card you summon by 3.

Description: A Normal/Hero card of your choosing gains +1 Attack.
EffectText: A Normal/Hero card of your choice gains 1 Attack.
ShortDescription: A Normal/Hero card of your choice gains 1 Attack.

Description: Your active Normal/Hero cards gain +5 Attack. When this card leaves the field your active Normal/Hero cards lose -8 Attack.
EffectText: Your Normal/Hero cards gain 5 Attack. When this card leaves the field, your Normal/Hero cards lose 8 Attack.
ShortDescription: Your Normal/Hero cards gain 5 Attack. When this card leaves the field, your Normal/Hero cards lose 8 Attack.

Description: Add one Equip Attribute Magic card from your Graveyard to your hand.
EffectText: Move 1 Magic Equip card from the Graveyard to your hand.
ShortDescription: Move 1 Magic Equip card from the Graveyard to your hand.

Description: The Cost of Magic cards is reduced by 1 for the Player.
EffectText: The Cost of your Magic cards is reduced by 1.
ShortDescription: The Cost of your Magic cards is reduced by 1.

Description: Discard 1 card to the Graveyard. You win the Battle this round.
EffectText: ...Carryover?
ShortDescription: ...Carryover?

Description:
Roll a six-sided dice and apply the result:
 1: Opposing Fighter gains +3 Attack.
 2: Your Fighter gains +3 Attack.
3: Opposing Fighter's Health is restored to its original value.
4: Your Fighter's Health is restored to its original value.
5: Your Fighter is Paralyzed.
6: Your Fighter gains Invincibility.
EffectText:
Roll a six-sided dice and apply the result:
 1: Opposing Fighter gains +3 Attack.
 2: Your Fighter gains +3 Attack.
3: Restore Opposing Fighter's Health.
4: Restore Your Fighter's Health.
5: Your Fighter is Paralyzed.
6: Your Fighter gains Invincibility.
ShortDescription:
Roll a six-sided dice and apply the result:
 1: Opposing Fighter gains +3 Attack.
 2: Your Fighter gains +3 Attack.
3: Restore Opposing Fighter's Health.
4: Restore Your Fighter's Health.
5: Your Fighter is Paralyzed.
6: Your Fighter gains Invincibility.

Description: Revive one card from either Player's Graveyard and add it to your hand. Upon resolving this card's effect, banish it.
EffectText: Add one card from either Graveyard to your hand, then banish this card.
ShortDescription: Add one card from either Graveyard to your hand, then banish this card.

Description: Special Summon one card from your Medical Bay to the field.
EffectText: Special Summon one card from your Medical Bay to the field.
ShortDescription: Special Summon one card from your Medical Bay to the field.

Description: Choose one card from either player's Medical Bay to heal and add it to your hand.
EffectText: Add one card from either Medical Bay to your hand.
ShortDescription: Add one card from either Medical Bay to your hand.

Description: Inflict 5 Life Points of Damage to the Opponent.
EffectText: Your opponent takes 5 damage.
ShortDescription: Your opponent takes 5 damage.

Description: Switch decks with your opponent (Med Bays are not switched). Your opponent gets to take 1 card from your hand (or field if no cards are in your hand) and add it to their own hand.
EffectText: Switch your Main Deck with your opponent. Your opponent may take 1 card from your hand (or the field if you have no cards in your hand) and add it to their own hand.
ShortDescription: Switch your Main Deck with your opponent. Your opponent may take 1 card from your hand (or the field if you have no cards in your hand) and add it to their own hand.

Description: When your opponent activates a Tech Card, play this card to force them to skip their next Draw during the Opening Phase.
EffectText:
Activate: Your opponent plays a Tech card.

Your opponent may not draw a card during their next Opening Phase.
ShortDescription:
Activate: Your opponent plays a Tech card.

Your opponent may not draw a card during their next Opening Phase.

Description: If the opposing Fighter has more attack strength than your Fighter has Health; Gain 7 Health if it allows you to survive.
EffectText:
Activate: The enemy Fighter is about to defeat you.

Gain 7 Health.
ShortDescription:
Activate: The enemy Fighter is about to defeat you.

Gain 7 Health.

Description: When equipped to your Fighter you may inflict Paralysis on the currently active opposing Fighter.
EffectText:
Activate: Equip to your Fighter.

The opposing Fighter is Paralyzed.
ShortDescription:
Activate: Equip to your Fighter.

The opposing Fighter is Paralyzed.

Description: Upon inflicting Life Point damage on the Opponent, they must discard their entire hand to the Graveyard/Medical Bay as appropriate.
EffectText:
Activate: Inflict Life Point damage.

Your opponent must discard their entire hand.
ShortDescription:
Activate: Inflict Life Point damage.

Your opponent must discard their entire hand.

Description: Activate when to Opponent summons a new Fighter to the field. The Fighter is immediately captured and sent to the Player's Medical Bay.
EffectText:
Activate: An enemy Fighter is summoned. 

The enemy Fighter is sent to your Medical Bay.
ShortDescription:
Activate: An enemy Fighter is summoned. 

The enemy Fighter is sent to your Medical Bay.

Description: All Normal and Hero cards owned by you gain +5 Health for the remainder of the game.
EffectText: Add 5 Health to all Normal/Hero cards you own.
ShortDescription: Add 5 Health to all Normal/Hero cards you own.

Description: The Opponent must re-roll any dice roll that results in a total greater than '4.'
EffectText: Your opponent may not roll higher than a 4.
ShortDescription: Your opponent may not roll higher than a 4.

Description: Duplicates the effect of one of the Opponent's active Tech cards. If Opponent has multiple Tech cards active, the Player can choose which card to mimic.
EffectText: Duplicates the effects of an active Opponents' Tech card of your choice.
ShortDescription: Duplicates the effects of an active Opponents' Tech card of your choice.

Description: Permanently increases your Summon Crest Rolls by +1.
EffectText: You gain an extra Summon Crest each turn.
ShortDescription: You gain an extra Summon Crest each turn.

Description: Permanently decreases your Summon Cost of cards by -1.
EffectText: The Cost of your cards is reduced by 1.
ShortDescription: The Cost of your cards is reduced by 1.

Description: Enhances the impact of your stat boosting card effects by +1.
EffectText: Cards that increase a value of one or more of your cards increase that value by 1.
ShortDescription: Cards that increase a value of one or more of your cards increase that value by 1.

Description: Enhances the effectiveness of your Equip cards by +1.
EffectText: Equip cards that increase a value of one or more of your cards increase that value by 1.
ShortDescription: Equip cards that increase a value of one or more of your cards increase that value by 1.

Description: Increases the Health of all your Normal and Hero cards by +3 at the start of each Standby Phase.
EffectText: The Health of your active cards increases by 3 when your Standby Phase starts.
ShortDescription: The Health of your active cards increases by 3 when your Standby Phase starts.

Description: When activated select one of your opponent's Equip card slots and disable it.
EffectText: You may disable one of your opponent's Equip card slots.
ShortDescription: You may disable one of your opponent's Equip card slots.

Description: Both Players must draw the top card from their Tech Deck and Activate it in their Tech Zone.
EffectText: Both Players must draw a card from their Tech Deck.
ShortDescription: Both Players must draw a card from their Tech Deck.
